This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on the problem of visual saliency. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a neural network architecture, which could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves image segmentation, which could potentially place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
